🚗The p.m. drop off will occur in the 𝐅𝐑𝐎𝐍𝐓 of the school building.
➡️ Please follow the traffic arrows in front of the middle school to reduce traffic during the elementary school’s dismissal from their a.m. session.
🏫 All pick-ups will occur in the rear of the school.

We can’t wait to see you Tuesday! #WeAreLB

Attached is a flyer advertising an LB community walk in. The Federal Education Law formerly known as No Child Left Behind, has recently been re-authorized as Every Student Succeeds Act (ESSA).

Join teachers, community members, students, and administrators at 7:00 a.m. at the LBHS flagpole for short remarks/commentary. Doughnuts and coffee will be served in the HS cafetorium afterwards.

Hope to see you there!
